Bailey's new retrospective is heavy on glamour.
The model Jerry Hall turned out for the private view of David Bailey’s newretrospectiveat London’s National Portrait Gallery – and here she is in 1983, her foot held by fashion photographer Helmut Newton. The image – shot in Cannes, France – is one of more than 250 taken by the British photographer that will be shown at Bailey’s Stardust when it opens on 6 February. Documenting a career that spans more than five decades, the photographs have been selected and arranged by Bailey – and cover travel and sculpture as well as fashion.If you would like to comment on this story or anything else you have seen on BBC Culture, head over to ourFacebookpage or message us onTwitter.